IL = International Culture
US = US Cultures


Meeting notes Examples:

1.	Meeting notes with a Paragraph style, \“stream of consciousness\”
Met today about switching into HCDD. Already finished IST 110 and IST 140, taking IST 210 now. Behind on GenEds — still needs GA and GN. Wants to pursue Graphic Design minor, asked if that pairs well with HCDD. We talked through entrance GPA requirement (2.7), and that change of major petition will be needed. Suggested schedule: IST 220 + GN course + support-of-option elective next semester.

2.	Meeting notes with bulleted list
•	Considering ETI path
•	Completed: IST 110, IST 210, IST 220
•	Needs: IST 256, IST 402, ENGL 202C
•	GenEds left: GA, GN
•	Asked if ENGL 202C can be done online summer
•	Wants internship in enterprise systems before senior year
•	Action: check summer sections of ENGL 202C, confirm prereq chain for IST 402
3.	Meeting notes with a Combination of paragraph + bullets, with abbreviations and slight spelling errors
Student is exploring cyber track. Still missing IST 220 and STAT200. Wants AI minor as well.
•	Taken: ist110, ist140, ist210
• Needs: GN x2, GA gen eds
• Planning to take ist256 + ist310 next fall (conflict w/ math220??)
• Mentioned overload of 18 cr, recorded keeping to 15-16 credits

4.	Meeting notes with a terse / shorthand / abbreviation-heavy style
mtg re: SRA. Done 110,210,220,256. Needs 432,402,440W. Still missing GN + GHW. Wants psych minor. Considering GN course in summer. note: AEC may limit adding another major.

5.	Meeting notes for course completion status
Met with John Doe on Oct 15th; pending prereqs are Q1, W2 . good possibility to complete them on time. Student doing well with the curriculum. Aspiring for pre-med. Plans to sign up life sciences major next semester. GenEds left: GA, GN. Definitely Needs: IST 256, IST 402, ENGL 202C. no retakes identified as all scores are high. Too early to comment on readiness to graduate but high probability based on current academic performance.


Below is the output that should be generated for the above meeting notes respectively: 
